Package ie.gmit.sw.base

Contains all base classes for compose all the services and interface classes.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CounterMap<K>
    An object that counts objects of type k.
    Identifiable
    Implemented for identify different instances of a class.
    Shingable
    Object intended for take lines of input from a file, separate them into strings shingles and return the hash code of those shingles.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractCosineCalculator
    Base class for calculate cosine distance, set the return type Callable<CosineDistanceResult>.
    Calculator
    Calculate the cosine distance of several CounterMap<Integer> , compare one CounterMap<Integer> against a queue of them, put results on another queue.
    ConcurrentCounterHashMap<K>
    Concurrent implementation of CounterMap using a HashMap.
    CosineCalculator
    Calculate cosine distance of 2 CounterMap<Integer> , works fine with not a big amount of shingles.
    CosineCalculatorBig
    Calculate cosine distance of two maps for big number of entrances.
    Counter
    Produce CounterMap<Integer>(which are a count of the selected type of shingles of each file) and place then in a output queue, take a array of File as parameter, for each file use a FileShinglerParser and MapBuilder for create the maps .
    CountOne
    Count shingles for one file, use for calculate counter map for query file.
    FileShingleParser
    Parse file into shingles, read file from IO and create shingles using Shingable object.
    GroupShingler
    Implementation of shingable for create a word group shingles.
    HashCounterMap<K>
    Not concurrent version of CounterMap, use a hash map for map objects with they count.
    KShingler
    Implementation of shingable that produce k-mers shingles.
    MapBuilder
    Base class for map builder.
    MutlipleThreadMapBuilder
    Builds map using multiple threads, take number shingles from a FileShingleParser and then several thread count those shingles using a CountingMap.
    SingleThreadMapBuilder
    Build map of shingles from a file using a single thread, good enough for the design because CounterMaps can counts one shingle at a time.
    Splite
    Contains split functions for group word shingles
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CosineCalculatorType
    Types of cosine calculator.
    ShingleType
    Type os shingles, Group are word groups and k_mers are character shingles.

Package ie.gmit.sw.base Description

Contains all base classes for compose all the services and interface classes.
